examples.en: She demanded payment in advance.
They demanded the right of assembly.
The customer demanded a refund.
Mr. Herbert demanded the yeas and nays.
Parents have demanded that the teacher resign.
He was an everlasting sympathy-seeker who demanded attention.
Clamoring multitudes demanded a view of the Pope.
She demanded to see the manager.
Come here at once! he demanded.
"Come here at once!" he demanded.
'Which one?' he demanded petulantly.
He demanded the name of the defunct.
They demanded it, and he acquiesced.
The bank demanded payment of the loan.
Why won't you answer me? she demanded.
The situation demanded immediate action.
"Why won't you answer me?" she demanded.
He demanded total control of the project.
They demanded some proof of my sincerity.
They demanded a free parliament and press.
Obstreperously, he demanded to get service.
The reporter demanded to see the documents.
'Where are you going?' she demanded angrily.
He demanded with much asperity what she meant.
The boss demanded that he be fired immediately.
The shareholders demanded a change in management.
Too many things demanded his attention at the same time.
The kidnappers demanded a ransom of one million dollars.
The opposing candidate has demanded equal time on television.
The appellate court demanded the production of all documents.
